ðŸŸ© 1. Strings
YAML supports plain and quoted strings.

# Plain string
name: John Doe

# Single-quoted string (no escaping needed)
message: 'Hello, world!'

# Double-quoted string (supports escape sequences like \n)
greeting: "Hello\nWorld"

# Multiline string using block scalars
description: |
  This is a multiline
  string that preserves
  line breaks.

note: >
  This is also a multiline
  string, but line breaks
  are folded into spaces.


ðŸŸ¦ 2. Lists (Sequences)
Inline List:

fruits: [apple, banana, cherry]
Block List:

fruits:
  - apple
  - banana
  - cherry

Lists can contain other lists or mappings too:
shopping:
  - item: Milk
    quantity: 2
  - item: Bread
    quantity: 1
ðŸŸ¨ 3. Mappings (Dictionaries / Key-Value Pairs)
Basic Mapping:
person:
  name: Alice
  age: 30
  city: New York


Inline Mapping:
person: {name: Alice, age: 30, city: New York}


Nested Mapping:
employee:
  name: Bob
  contact:
    email: bob@example.com
    phone: 1234567890


âœ… Combined Example

title: "Bookstore"

books:
  - title: "1984"
    author: "George Orwell"
    genres: [Dystopian, Political Fiction]
  - title: "To Kill a Mockingbird"
    author: "Harper Lee"
    genres:
      - Fiction
      - Classic
